omputed in the child when the ClassFile is loaded. I’m curious if I can modify bytes, especially since the current VM is Java 11.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Java 17 Accessibility**\\n\\nI’m noting that in Java 17, using `setAccessible(true)` requires the `add-opens` option to be present, which is good to know. This is a helpful detail for properly managing module accessibility changes that come with Java 17. I’m curious how this impacts the code's functionality and security. Understanding these requirements will definitely make working with Java modules smoother. I'll need to remember this when dealing with accessibility in my future projects!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_8wa6M6SlvOrprj7FQ1KXJ2Ve|fc_01935a689215c57c0169ef57f397188194910c620ee360869a", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.javassist/javassist/3.24.1-GA/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/javassist-security-actions-3-tests/reflect-config.json", "limit": 80}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2547, "output": 2731, "cacheRead": 24064, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 29342, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777293258656, "responseId": "resp_01935a689215c57c0169ef57cb2a988194ae8331f24f9efb69"}}
